      {
        "type": "Definition",
        "content": "1. The process of creation.\n2. The gradual diminishing of G-d’s light to create all of spiritual and physical existence, and then to be revealed within this creation.\n3. Literally: The Order of Progression.\nBasic Seder Hishtalshelus\nChassidus gives a basic Seder Hishtalshelus for beginners:\nOriginally, there was “Him and His name alone.” That is, the Essence of the Infinite One blessed be He and His light and ray, which are called His name. Everything was included in His essence in an infinite manner and it filled the “empty place.” Then, Gd contracted His light and left only an impression in this void. Then, from this impression, He drew forth a thin line of light into the empty place first as ten circles and then ten straight sefiros.\nThe light before the contraction is called the Upper Purity and the first circle of light at the beginning of the line is called the Lower Purity.\nAfter this, the kingship of the Infinite contracted to become the crown of the Original Man.\nThen, from kingship of the Original Man came the crown to ancient days.\nThen, from the kingship of long face came the crown to father and mother and from the kingship of father and mother came the crown to small face and from small face to female.\nUntil, from the kingship of Emanation came the crown to Creation and so too from Creation to Formation and from Formation to Actualization. Finally arriving at the kingship of kingship of Actualization—the end of the entire progression."
      },
      {
