        "content": "•\tBefore taking a trip by train one needs a map of the stations.\nIn former generations young men were not admitted to hear maamarim being delivered by the Rebbe of their generation. They first had to be familiar at least with the Seder Hishtalshelus, at least to know all of its stations…. Nowadays, when everyone is admitted, people ought to be grateful and should listen attentively. (Likkutei Dibburim 39 (2), 1)\n•\tA chain contains many links, but they all act as a single unit. Tug the top and the bottom moves. Tug the bottom and the top moves.\nBasic Hishtalshelus Reference Chart\n#\nName of Stage\nSoul – Body Metaphor\nLanguage Metaphor\n1\nעצמות אור אין סוף\nAtzmus Ohr Ein Sof\nEssence of Infinite Light\nיחידה – the essence of your soul.\nYour inner Self, which transcends all forms and expressions, but contains them all and pervades them all. (Such as desire, intellect, emotion, thought, speech, and action.)\nThis includes taste and style.\nDirect experience beyond expression.\n(Inner Self of author or speaker.\nSelf-expression automatically present in language.)\nIncludes aspects that can be expressed.\n2\nצמצום\nTzimtzum\nContraction\nFocused Choice.\nThe ability of focusing and limiting the Self to one desire or expression.\nFocus.\nLimiting content of expression to something specific and conveyable.\n3\nרשימו\nReshimu\nImpression\nThe aspect of Self left in one’s choices, giving an “impression” of one’s taste and style.\n(As in making an “impression” on people.)\nSymbol.\nPower to hide or represent an idea in a symbol.\n4\nקו\nKav\nLine\nFlexible Choice.\nYour ability to change, respond, assess, and interact.\nOrder.\nAbility of symbols to express ideas by stringing them in a line.\n5\nרצון הקדום\nRatzon HaKadom\nOriginal Desire (First Circle)\nYour inner abstract desire for life, happiness and fulfillment.\nAxiom.\nThe basic premise that is the foundation of all of the points made. The general view and approach.\n6\nעשר ספירות דעיגולים\nEsser Sfirot D’Igulim\nTen Circle Sefiros\nYour inner abstract desires for each of your ten faculties.\nThe subconscious.\nMoral.\nThe essential points trying to be conveyed.\n7\nאדם קדמון\nAdam Kadmon\nOriginal Man (Straight Sefiros)\nSelf-image and world-view.\nInterface of subconscious and conscious.\nThe association of the abstract inner desire to a concrete image based on the world.\nHow you define yourself in terms of the world, and the world in terms of you.\nMeaning.\nThe inner meaning of words, including metaphors, associations, and representation.\n8\nאצילות\nAtzilus\nEmanation\nYour consciousness as expressed in your body.\nConscious desires, intellect, and emotions and their physical expression in the organs.\nMessage.\nThe intent trying to be conveyed in language.\n8.1\nעתיק יומין\nAtik Yomin\nAncient Days\nYour fun leisure side.\nPleasure.\nFulfillment.\nExpression of pleasure in language.\nFor example, a joke.\n8.2\nאריך אנפין\nArich Anpin\nLong Face\nYour big hopes, dreams, and desires side.\nDesire.\nGoals.\nExpression of desire in language.\nFor example, “Please pass the salt.”\n8.3\nאבא\nAba\nFather\nYour creative and intuitive side.\nInsight.\nIntellect.\nExpression of creativity and insight in language.\n8.4\nאימא\nIma\nMother\nYour logical side.\nUnderstanding.\nRationality.\nExpression of logic and understanding in language.\n8.5\nזעיר אנפין\nZeir Anpin\nSmall Face\nYour day-to-day personality side.\nEmotions.\nResponsiveness.\nExpression of emotions in language.\n8.6\nנוקבא\nNukva\nFemale\nYour expressive side.\nPower of thought, speech, and action.\nExpressiveness.\nExpression of eloquence in language.\n9\nמסך\nMasach\nCurtain\nLanguage Barrier.\nThe privacy of your consciousness, thoughts and emotions hiding them behind the curtain of your external expressions in speech and action.\nLanguage Barrier.\nThe need to communicate through a medium.\n10\nבריאה\nBriyah\nCreation\nThought.\nConcept.\nThought Language.\nDefinition of the words.\nLanguage as symbols for ideas.\n11\nיצירה\nYetzirah\nFormation\nSpeech.\nForm.\nSpoken Language.\nSounds.\n12\nעשיה\nAsiyah\nActualization\nAction.\nWritten Language.\nInk on paper.\nEtched in stone."
